<title>MILNET:  Terrorism - List of Assassinations</title>
<center>
<img src="milnet.gif" align=middle, alt="Milnet">
<p>
<p>
<a href="milnet.htm"><img src="milico.gif" align=middle alt="Milnet Main"></a>
<a href="terror.htm"><img src="terror.gif" align=middle alt="Terrorism"></a>
<p>
<p></center>
<H1>List of Assassinations, 1968-
1986</H1>
<P>
8/28/68:  U.S. Ambassador to Guatamala was killed in a "drive by assassination" the sole 
victim of his attackers.<P>
9/9/72:  Tthe Israeli Counsel in London was killed by a letter bomb.<P>
1973:  Prime Minister of Spain, Carreo Blanco, was the sole victim of an asassination 
attempt.<P>
12/75:  Terrorists attacked a meeting of the OPEC counsel killing 3 and injuring many 
others.<P>
1977:  Hanns-Martin Schleyer, a German industrialist was kidnapped and murdered in 1977 
by the Banner Meinhoff gang.  The kidnap was both politically motivated and one in which a 
ransom was demanded.<P>
03/78:  Political candidate for President Aldo Moro of Italy was kidnapped and murdered, 
thus crippling the election process of that country in March of 1978.<P>
1979:  Unidentified authorities broke up an assassination attempt on the the NATO 
commander, General Alexander Haig in Brussels in 1979.  Although not a major political 
contender, Haig was an important cabinet member for both Nixon and Reagan, so this 
assassination attempt could have had a major effect on future U.S. government 
activities.<P>
1979:  In one of many political assassinations in the U.K.,  a M.P. (member of Parliment), 
Airey Neave was killed by a car bomb in 1979.<P>
1981:  Assassination attempt on Pope John Paul failed, but seriously wounded the pontiff in 
the summer of 1981.<P>
10/6/81:  Anwar Sadat killed by a bomb in his reviewing stand while his troops marched by in 
review on October 6, 1981.   Numerous injuries in the reviewing stand and the whole affair 
was taped and televised around the world.<P>
11/12/81, attempt on Christian Chapmen.<P>
1/16/83:  Lt. Col. Robert Fay assassinated in Lebannon, UN peacekeeping force 
commander, on January 16, 1982.<P>
12/14/82:  Bashir Gemayel, President Elect of Lebanon, assassinated via a bomb on 
September 14, 1982.<P>
9/30/83:  63 killed in the bombing of the American Embassy in Beirut on September 30, 
1983.  <P>
10/23/83:  3 weeks later,  the same M.O.as used in the American Embasssy in Beirut, a truck 
bomb, was used to kill 241 Marines at the Marine Barracks in Beirut, Lebanon, on October 
23, 1983.<P>
1986:  Leamon Hunt, United Nations Director General killed.<P>
2/6/86:   Admiral Christobal Colon (direct descendant of Christopher Columbus) was killed in 
Spain by a  Basque Separtist  group.<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
<P>
