<title>Research Relevant to Early Childhood Care and
Development</title>
<body BGCOLOR="FFFFE0" TEXT="800000" LINK="8E2323" 
VLINK=""0000FF">
<h1> Research Relevant to Early Childhood Care and
Development </h1> ( This section is still being developed.  We are preparing a
text describing item in the outline, with examples) 
     
<h3>I.  Basic Research</h3>
<ul>
	Psychological Research<br>
	Educational Research<br>
	Health, Nutrition, Physiology<br>
	Research from the social sciences
	<ul>	
		Sociology and Demography<br>
		Anthropology<br>
		Economics<br>
		Women&#146;s Studies
</ul>
</ul>
<h3>II.  Project/Program Evaluation and Monitoring</h3>
<ul>
	Situation Analyses: Analyzing the social context, the status of children, and
the availability 		of resources (institutional, human, technological,
financial, legal)<br>
	Monitoring<br>
<ul>
		Specific Programs: (Did I do what I planned to do?  If not, why not?)<br>
		National commitments and changes (see indicators)<br>
</ul>	
Formative Evaluations<br>
<ul>	
	Of processes (Do the activities/processes work well?  If not, why not?)<br>
		Of effects (Did the activities have an effect?  If not, why not?)<br>
</ul>	
Summative Evaluations <br>
<ul>	
	(Did the program have an impact?)
</ul>

<a href=chile.html>An Inter-agency Workshop on Evaluation and Costs of
Early Childhood Programmes in Latin America and the Caribbean</a>
</ul>
<h3>III.  Research Methodologies</h3>
<ul>
	Experimental and quasi-experimental studies<br>
	Participatory research or evaluation<br>
	Ethnographic/anthropological research<br>
	Longitudinal research<br>
	Cost-effectiveness or cost-benefit studies<br>
	Case studies
</ul>
<h3>IV.  Assessment/Measurement/Indicators</h3>
<ul>
		Measuring child development<br>
	Measuring program costs and benefits<br>
<a href=kili.html>TOWARDS AN ANALYSIS OF THE COSTS AND EFFECTIVENESS
    OF COMMUNITY-BASED EARLY CHILDHOOD EDUCATION IN KENYA</a>


                              

                                    by

                               Robert G. Myers,

                           

                                February 1992<p>

<a href=analyzi.html>Analyzing Costs Of Community-Based
Early Childhood Development Projects</a> by Robert G. Myers.
A paper prepared for the &#147;Workshop on Evaluation and Costs of Early
Childhood Development Programmes in Latin America and the Caribbean&#148;.<p>

	At risk indicators<br>
	Monitoring indicators at a national level<br>
<a href=analysis.html>Analysis of Instruments Used in Latin America
to Measure Psychosocial Development in Children From 0 to 6 Years of Age</a> by Lucille C. Atkin

</ul>
<h3>V.  Dissemination and Use of Research and Evaluations</h3>
<h3>VI.  Research Reviews, Periodicals, Bibliographies</h3>
<h3>VII.  Research Organizations </h3>

