<h1>Networks: Regional and Coalition-based</h1>  
<h3>The CG: a Network of Networks</h3>  
The Consultative Group is a network of networks concerned with young
children and their families.  Each participant of the CG represents one or
several networks of development groups, family service networks, programme
developers, NGOs, researchers, regional capacity-building coalitions, and
international initiative  efforts.  We try, to the best of our ability, to
gather information on the efforts of these diverse networks, and to disseminate
that information through our contact people.  Our aim is to help promote
collaboration, information and resource sharing, south-south dialogue, inter
and intra regional dialogue, and most important: better, more integrated
programming for young children and their families.  <br>
  <br>
	In this section of the Web Site, we need your help to collect the best, most
useful information about what is happening within the diverse regions of the
world and within the networks you represent.  Please send us 
<A HREF="mailto:info@ecdgroup.com">e-mail </A>or faxes
(U.S.: 413- 268-7279) letting us know about the child, family and community
focussed networks you participate in that might be relevant to the participants
of the Consultative Group (we want to hear about networks that are
communicating through traditional channels such as print media, phone and fax,
as well as those which are on-line). 
 E-mail: 
<A HREF="mailto:info@ecdgroup.com">info@ecdgroup.com</A>
  <br><p>
 <hr>
