<head></head><body><title>The Education For All Initiative </title>
<h1>The Education For All Initiative (EFA)</h1> 
 
 <A HREF="introefa.html">Introduction to the EFA and its relevance for young children.
</A><p>
 <A HREF="efadoc.html">The World Declaration on Education for All: Meeting Basic Learning Needs.
</A>Excerpts from the text of the World Declaration on EFA<b> </b>the related
&#147;Framework for Action to Meet Basic Learning Needs.&#148; <b>
</b><p>
 <A HREF="bennett4.html">Educating Young Children: A Broader Vision.  </A>By John Bennett,
Coordinator of the Early Childhood and Family Programmes at UNESCO.
	A description of the EFA and a discussion of how the EFA effects young
children and their families.  Summaries of several EFA-inspired
programmes.	<p>
 <A HREF="eccdbob.html">Creating the Foundation Stones for Education for All: Action Initiatives in
Early Childhood Care and Development.</A> By Robert G. Myers.
	After the EFA Forum in Jomtien, Thailand and a follow up meeting in New
Delhi, representatives of several key institutions concerned with ECCD met to
create a plan of action for promoting programming for young children and their
families in response to the EFA Declaration.  This article outlines and
discusses the lines of action laid out in the plan of action. <p>
<b> Three Case Studies presented at the EFA Followup Meeting in New Delhi -
</b><ul>
<IMG SRC="blue.gif" ALT ="*"><A HREF="lessons.html">Introduction: Lessons learned. </A><br>
<IMG SRC="blue.gif" ALT ="*"><A HREF="casvenez.html"> Venezuela.  Programs Hogares De Cuidado Diario: Plan De Extension
Masiva (Family Day-care Homes Program: Massive Extension 		Plan).</A><br>
<IMG SRC="blue.gif" ALT ="*"><A HREF="caskenya.html"> Kenya.  A Case Study of Early Childhood Care and Education in 		Kenya.
</A> <br>
<IMG SRC="blue.gif" ALT ="*"><A HREF="casphili.html"> Philippines.  Parents as Learners: Toward Partnerships and
Participation. </A><br>
</ul>
 <IMG SRC="blue.gif" ALT ="*"><A HREF="efainfo.html">
Related Resources for EFA Information </A><p>
