<u>CHILD DEVELOPMENT INDICATORS</u><p>
<p>
<u>Cognitive Measures</u><p>
<p>
IQ Scores:  The Stanford-Binet; Goodenough Draw-a-Person test<p>
Cognitive Development: Piaget Seriation and Classification tasks<p>
Complexity of Behavior: Tizard six-level rating scale of observation<p>
Cognitive Style and Analytical Thinking: Children&#146;s Embedded Figures Test
and WIPPSY &#147;Analytical Triad&#148;<p>
Academic Achievement: Test of Turkish, arithmetic and general ability<p>
School Achievement: Report cards and school adjustment records<p>
<p>
<u>MEASURES OF CHILD PERSONALITY AND SOCIAL DEVELOPMENT</u><p>
<p>
Autonomy-Dependence: Observation ratings and Mother interview <p>
Aggression: Observation ratings and mother interview <p>
Delay of Gratification: Mischel procedure <p>
Self Concept/Self Esteem: Draw-a Person test; Larsen and Leigh Index; Mother
interview<p>
Emotional Indicators: Draw-a-Person test<p>
Level of School Participation: Tizard six-level rating scale of observations<p>
School Adjustment/Liking: Mother interview<p>
