Attachment D<p>
<p>
<p>
<b><u>SUMMARY OF ACTIVITIES AND DOCUMENTS PRODUCED FOR</u></b><p>
<b><u>PARTICIPANTS IN THE CONSULTATIVE GROUP</u></b><p>
<b></b><p>
<b>September 1983 to December, 1986</b><p>
<b></b><p>
<b><u>The Knowledge Network</u></b><p>
<p>
	A Knowledge Network has grown to include approximately 400 individuals in 90
countries. An attempt has been made to locate individuals who are themselves
"brokers" of information. Three issues of a bulletin called the
<u>Coordinators' Notebook</u> have been produced and mailed, together with
several reprints of articles, studies, and photocopies of tables of contents
from periodicals in the field. The response to these mailings has been high and
encouraging.<p>
<p>
<p>
<b>Newsletter: The Coordinators' Notebook</b><p>
<p>
<b><u>Completed</u></b><p>
<p>
	1. <b>Issue No. 1</b>, October 1985, 28 pages, Focus: Information at Your
Service.<p>
<p>
	2. I<b>ssue No. 2</b>, April 1986, 28 pages, Focus: Programme Options.<p>
<p>
	3. <b>Issue No. 3</b>, 0ctober 1986, 24 pages, Focus: A Rationale for
Investing in Early Childhood.<p>
<p>
<b><u>In Progress</u></b><p>
	1. <b>Issue No. 4</b>, January 1987, 3 pages, Focus: Home-

based
programmes.<p>
<p>
<p>
